Both PersistLogProcessor or PersistStoreProcessor should work in 1.14.4 
for duplication reduction purposes.

Which to use depends on whether you want to carry-forward to future 
crawls a log of prior URL history (which can be preloaded in a 
time-consuming step at crawl-start), or a full &#39;state&#39; BDB environment 
directory (perhaps slimmed via an offline copy of just the &#39;history&#39; info).

If you had a problem trying to use both PersistLoadProcessor and 
PersistStoreProcessor in the same crawl, it may have been a 
configuration mistake, or a new bug. If you can supply more details 
about your configuration and the error you saw, we might be able to get 
to the bottom of the issue. One thing to watch out for: any state 
directory provided as a &#39;preload-source&#39; should *not* also be the target 
state directory for the current crawl.

- Gordon @ IA

